definition.value: A dioxo monocarboxylic acid consisting of 6-phenylhexanoic acid having the two oxo groups at the 2- and 6-positions.
An aconitate(3-) that is the conjugate base of trans-aconitic acid.

A linear amino tetrasaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl, beta-D-galactosyl and N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine residues linked glycosidically in a (1->3), (1->3) and (1->4) sequence.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a docosasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked two beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl linear nonasaccharide units [linked (1->3) and (1->6)], while to the N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue at the reducing end is linked (1->6) an alpha-L-fucose residue.
A quaternary ammonium ion that is nitrogen substituted by three methyl groups and a 2-oxoethyl group. It is an intermediate in the metabolism of amino acids like glycine, serine and threonine.
